text:
01 of 79 NAOMI CAMPBELL WWD/REX/Shutterstock The 47-year-old supermodel proves she's still the reigning catwalk queen at the Azzedine Alaïa show.

02 of 79 KARLIE KLOSS WWD/REX/Shutterstock "Thank you @azzedinealaiaofficial for inspiring me (and the entire world!) with the passion and love that you bring to all that you do," Kloss shared on Instagram of working with the designer on his latest show.

03 of 79 CÉLINE DION Mireya Acierto/GC Images Next up on the Céline takes couture tour, the icon steps out in a bow-embellished Dice Kayek blouse, Céline pants and bag from the upcoming Céline Dion collection.

04 of 79 MICHELLE RODRIGUEZ Bertrand Rindoff Petroff/Getty The actress goes black tie in a glittering midnight blue gown at the Azzedine Alaïa show.

05 of 79 LILY ALDRIDGE Julien Hekimian/Getty No bra, no problem. The supermodel shows off her super-sternum in a blazer (with nothing underneath) teamed with black slacks at the Vogue Foundation Dinner.

06 of 79 BELLA HADID KCS Presse / MEGA This is probably the most covered up we've seen Bella since she landed in Paris for Couture Week.

07 of 79 LILY JAMES Marc Piasecki/WireImage "Thank you @burberry for this icy blue sequined gem," James captioned a photo of her glittering gown, worn to the Vogue Foundation Dinner, on Instagram.

08 of 79 BELLA HADID Continuing her "naked" Couture week, Bella skips the bra under her sheer blue gown on the Fendi runway.

09 of 79 KENDALL JENNER PATRICK KOVARIK/AFP/Getty Kendall has a more modest moment on the Fendi catwalk in a caped black dress and fur-trim ankle booties.

10 of 79 KARL LAGERFELD PATRICK KOVARIK/AFP/Getty Images The fashion legend takes his final bow on the Fendi runway -- and even manages a slight smile.

11 of 79 OLIVIA PALERMO AND JOHANNES HUEBL The couture couple were clearly made for each other, as they prove in coordinating Valentino looks at the label's show.

12 of 79 COCO ROCHA Who needs to walk down the runway when you can ride down it in your own high-fashion tricycle as Coco Rocha does in the Jean-Paul Gaultier show.

13 of 79 COCO ROCHA AND JEAN PAUL-GAULTIER Rocha (in a gold unitard) joins the designer and a young model to close out the show.

14 of 79 VIKTOR & ROLF MODEL Some models in the Viktor & Rolf show wore giant doll heads to match their couture looks.

15 of 79 NICKY HILTON The star teamed her pink caped mini with a very summery braid at the Valentino show.

16 of 79 ALESSANDRA MASTRONARDI AND AZIZ ANSARI Bertrand Rindoff Petroff/Getty The Master of None stars dress to impress at the Chanel show.

17 of 79 IAN BOHEN AND JACKIE CRUZ The TV stars took in the style action front row Jean-Paul Gaultier show.

18 of 79 CARLA BRUNI-SARKOZY The former French first lady proves the style power of a sleek black jumpsuit (which she teams with a Bulgari bag) at the Jean Paul-Gaultier show.

19 of 79 ISABELLE HUPPERT The French actress still managed to look très chic in a pair of blue jeans and a simple white cape at the Jean-Paul Gaultier show.

20 of 79 BACKSTAGE AT JEAN-PAUL GAULTIER The designer feels the love from his front row fans including Blanca Li, Catherine Deneuve, Farida Khelfa, Carla Bruni-Sarkozy and Rossy de Palma.

21 of 79 CAMILA COELHO The fashion and beauty blogger puts a street style twist on this Elie Saab star-print tulle mini at the label's show.

22 of 79 NAOMI WATTS AND SOPHIA LOREN Bertrand Rindoff Petroff/Getty We imagine that Naomi was totally fangirling at the moment this photo was taken, as she sits next to the silver screen queen herself at the Armani Privé show.

23 of 79 FRONT ROW AT ARMANI PRIVÉ Bertrand Rindoff Petroff/Getty Naomi Watts, Sophia Loren, Roberta Armani and Kate Winslet are what FROW dreams are mad of.

24 of 79 KENDALL JENNER Marc Piasecki/WireImage The supermodel hasn't been hitting too many runways in Paris, but she is all over the red carpet, seen here in a chic mini dress, $1 million worth of Lorraine Schwartz Jewelry and a chic top knot at the Vogue Foundation Dinner.

25 of 79 BELLA HADID Starface/Splash News The model opened the show for her designer and friend Alexandre Vauthier in a sheer mesh turtleneck, maxi skirt, and military-inspired cap.

26 of 79 BELLA HADID Chesnot/Getty And she didn't stop there. She also hit the Alexandre Vauthier catwalk in a plunging silver gown with a slit-up-to-there.

27 of 79 PRIYANKA CHOPRA Antonio de Moraes Barros Filho/WireImage The actress selects a chic LWD and black heels for the Armani Privé show.

28 of 79 KATE WINSLET Stephane Cardinale /Corbis/Getty And Winslet opts an LBD at the show.

29 of 79 NAOMI WATTS Stephane Cardinale/Corbis/Getty The actress pairs an ivory slip dress with a matching blazer and nude sandals at the Armani Privé show.

30 of 79 KIRSTEN DUNST Marc Piasecki/WireImage The actress's black velvet gown (worn to the Vogue Foundation Dinner) may be demure on top, but the skirt is covered in sheer panels.

31 of 79 KARLIE KLOSS Marc Piasecki/WireImage Now that she's platinum, the supermodel has been experimenting with her makeup look, selecting a vampy, deep purple lipstick to go with her asymmetrical black gown and Repossi jewelry at the Vogue Foundation Dinner.

32 of 79 ZENDAYA Marc Piasecki/GC Images The Vogue covergirl continues her high-fashion style streak in Paris in high-fashion Viktor and Rolf sweatshirt dress, and a effortless top knot. "I did not do my hair at all," she joked on Twitter.

33 of 79 BARBARA PALVIN The model keeps it chic and sleek in a black suit and a red lip at the Armani Privé show.

34 of 79 BELLA HADID Marc Piasecki/WireImage Tangerine dream! Spring 2017 Couture dress with a head-turning train at the Vogue Foundation Dinner.

35 of 79 DOUTZEN KROES Marc Piasecki/WireImage The model knows the power of an LBD as she proves in a this fit-and-flare mini (teamed with platform sandals and a red lip) at the Vogue Foundation Dinner.

36 of 79 KATE MOSS Marc Piasecki/WireImage The model icon attends the Vogue Foundation Dinner in a chic black suit featuring a blazer with crystal-covered lapels.

37 of 79 BELLA HADID WWD/REX/Shutterstock Walking down yet another catwalk, Hadid completely transforms her look at the Maison Margiela show.

38 of 79 KRISTEN STEWART Stephane Cardinale/Corbis/Getty After making her mark at the Chanel show in a glittering onesie, Stewart goes for another sexy look, wearing a sequin-covered black micromini and ankle-strap pumps to the launch party for Chanel's new perfume "Gabrielle."

39 of 79 STELLA MAXWELL Stephane Cardinale/Corbis/Getty The model joins Stewart at the Chanel perfume launch, wearing black ripped skinnies and a sequin cropped jacket.

40 of 79 EMILY RATAJKOWSKI BACKGRID Jewel tone velvets are going to be huge trend this fall, and the model is clearly getting a jumpstart on the look in her emerald J. Brand two piece teamed with a black bandeau and a new bag from her upcoming collection.

41 of 79 LOTTIE MOSS Jacopo Raule/Getty When you're at a Bulgari pop up shop event in Paris, you have to be holding one of the brand's chic bags, and the model got the memo waring her pink-and-white striped purse with a textured strapless cocktail dress.

42 of 79 KAROLINA KURKOVA Marc Piasecki/WireImage The model's legging boots were definitely made for walking, and that fringe dress, worn to the Vogue Foundation Dinner, was made for Boomerang-ing.

43 of 79 EMILY RATAJKOWSKI KCS Presse/MEGA The model attends the Vogue Foundation Dinner in a sexy black gown and effortless updo.

44 of 79 ALICIA VIKANDER Splash News Online The actress adds Bulgari accessories to her black lace dress at the brand's pop up shop event in Paris.

45 of 79 KATY PERRY AND CARA DELEVINGNE Stephane Cardinale/Corbis/Getty The stars (and their platinum buzz cuts) spend July 4th together at the Chanel show in Paris, one year after Cara spent the weekend in Rhode Island at Taylor Swift's epic July 4th party.

46 of 79 CARA AND KATY (CONT.) Bertrand Rindoff Petroff/Getty And of course, they're wearing their couture best for the occasion.

47 of 79 KRISTEN STEWART Stephane Cardinale/Corbis/Getty K-Sizzle. The Chanel muse selects a glittering, second-skin onesie and sky-high pumps at the label's fall/winter 2018 Haute Couture show.

48 of 79 MARY AND KATY PERRY Pascal Le Segretain/Getty The singer brings a very special plus one to the Chanel show -- her mom Mary.

49 of 79 JULIANNE MOORE AND KRISTEN STWEART Bertrand Rindoff Petroff/Getty The actresses (who starred together in Still Alice) reunite front row at the Chanel show.

50 of 79 CARA DELEVINGNE Bertrand Rindoff Petroff/Getty It wouldn't be a Chanel event without the model-turned-actress, who owns her edgy style off the runway as a front row guest.

51 of 79 JULIANNE MOORE Pascal Le Segretain/Getty Très chic! Moore makes her mark at the Chanel show in one of the French's label's signature tweed mini dresses.

52 of 79 TRACEE ELLIS ROSS Bertrand Rindoff Petroff/Getty The actress continues her couture week takeover in chic allover white with red accents (perhaps her nod to the 4th of July).

53 of 79 TILDA SWINTON Pascal Le Segretain/Getty Swinton has her own brand of style swagger, which she shows at the Chanel show in chic white separates, including a belted coat, floor-skimming maxi skirt and gold loafers.

54 of 79 CLAUDIA SCHIFFER Pascal Le Segretain/Getty From the catwalk to the frow, the forever Chanel girl attends the show in a black zip-front jumpsuit teamed with It girl accessories.

55 of 79 PHARRELL WILLIAMS AND HELEN LASICHANH Bertrand Rindoff Petroff/Getty The couple that Chanels together, stays together.

56 of 79 LILY COLLINS Pascal Le Segretain/Getty The star braves a denim moment in a pair of cropped jeans teamed with a fringe embellished Chanel top and ankle-strap sandals.

57 of 79 KATY PERRY AND PHARRELL WILLIAMS Pascal Le Segretain/Getty Because they're happy (they're wearing Chanel).

58 of 79 KATY PERRY, KARL LAGERFELD, CARA DELEVINGNE AND CLAUDIA SCHIFFER Dominique Charriau/WireImage Presenting the many muses of Chanel Kaiser Karl Lagerfeld at his latest show.

59 of 79 ROWAN BLANCHARD Bertrand Rindoff Petroff/Getty The 15-year-old star almost wore a "cupcake dress" to the Chanel show, but in the end she has a chic menswear moment in a embellished tweed jumpsuit with a matching cropped blazer.

60 of 79 JENNIFER LAWRENCE Dominique Charriau/WireImage The Dior darling reps the brand hard (she's a long-time ambassador), attending the show in a head-to-toe look including a white lace mini dress, fringe sweater, wide-brim hat, embellished bag and sneakers that go up her calf.

61 of 79 JENNIFER LAWRENCE PART 2 GEOFFROY VAN DER HASSELT/AFP/Getty Images First the show, then the after party. Lawrence wears a sheer skirt with exposed "Dior" briefs and fringe top to the opening of the Dior exhibition marking the 70th anniversary of Christian Dior.

62 of 79 CÉLINE DION Pierre Suu/Getty Images The eternal fashion icon brings her sartorial A-Game to the Giambattista Valli show (and some serious cheering to the front row).

63 of 79 BELLA HADID Jacopo Raule/Getty Images for Christian Dior Another fashion week, another naked gown for Bella, seen here on the red carpet at the Dior 70th anniversary exhibition party.

64 of 79 ELLE FANNING Pascal Le Segretain/Getty Images The Beguiled star has a major mini moment in a pink Miu Miu design covered in oversized paillettes at the label's cruise collection show.

65 of 79 ZENDAYA Samir Hussein/Samir Hussein/WireImage Better from the back! Zendaya goes full on glam in an all white Ralph & Russo Couture look and Chopard earrings at the label's show, and outfit which she describes as "fit for a princess."

66 of 79 CARA DELEVINGNE Pascal Le Segretain/Getty Images for Christian Dior Proving over-the-knee boots are here to stay, Delevingne teams her flirty white mini with some daring black thigh-highs at the Dior exhibition.

67 of 79 NATALIE PORTMAN Antonio de Moraes Barros Filho/WireImage Portman opts for a chic LWD at the Dior exhibtion launch.

68 of 79 KIRSTEN DUNST Dominique Charriau/WireImage Dunst has a Dior moment at the show in a black embroidered dress covered in a star print.

69 of 79 JENNIFER LAWRENCE, NATALIE PORTMAN AND ROBERT PATTINSON Bertrand Rindoff Petroff/Getty Images The trio brings someA-list star wattage to the Dior show.

70 of 79 KARLIE KLOSS "Went platinum without the album," the model says of her new white blonde hue, which she debuted at the Dior show.

71 of 79 KARLIE KLOSS PART 2 Jacopo Raule/Getty Images for Christian Dior She also pulls quick change, putting on another head-turning Dior dress for the label's 70th anniversary party.

72 of 79 KENDALL JENNER, JOAN SMALLS AND BELLA HADID Pascal Le Segretain/Getty Images The model squad poses backstage at the Miu Miu Cruise Collection show.

73 of 79 FELICITY JONES Jacopo Raule/Getty Images for Christian Dior Jones keeps it simple in a black, belted dress the Dior 70th anniversary exhibition.

74 of 79 EVA HERZIGOVA The model wears the new It Dior accessory (that hat!) with a chic black gown and fashion draped blazer at the 70th anniversary exhibition ecent.

75 of 79 ELIZABETH OLSEN Stephane Cardinale - Corbis/Corbis via Getty Images What's black and white and chic all over? The actress's two piece set worn to the Dior show.

76 of 79 WINNIE HARLOW Jacopo Raule/Getty Images for Christian Dior The model of the moment wears a romantic gray lace gown to the Dior 70th anniversary exhibition.

77 of 79 BIANCA JAGGER Dominique Charriau/WireImage The fashion icon doesn't let the heat in Paris prevent her from wearing a velvet coat dress at the Dior show.

78 of 79 GEMMA ARTERTON Stephane Cardinale - Corbis/Corbis via Getty Images The actress wears a white suit over a sexy black bandeau at the Dior show.
